50|$|The ECGC Limited (Formerly Export Credit Guarantee Corporation of India Ltd) is {{a company}} wholly owned by the Government of India based in Mumbai, Maharashtra. It {{provides}} <b>export</b> credit <b>insurance</b> support to Indian exporters and {{is controlled by the}} Ministry of Commerce. Government of India had initially set up <b>Export</b> Risks <b>Insurance</b> Corporation (ERIC) in July 1957. It was transformed into Export Credit and Guarantee Corporation Limited (ECGC) in 1964 and to Export Credit Guarantee Corporation of India in 1983.|$|R
